# 🎮 Game Design Chapter — Resource Guide

A curated list of free resources to support your learning across all chapter sessions.
No experience needed — everything here is beginner-friendly unless noted.

---

## 🎬 YouTube Tutorials (by topic)

### Blender & 3D Modelling
- [Blender Guru — Beginner Series](https://www.youtube.com/@blenderguru) — The classic starting point for absolute beginners
- [CG Fast Track](https://www.youtube.com/@CGFastTrack) — Fast, structured Blender tutorials
- [Grant Abbitt](https://www.youtube.com/@GrantAbbitt) — Low poly characters and game-ready assets
- [Stylized Station](https://www.youtube.com/@StylizedStation) — Stylised art and texturing for games
- [Imphenzia](https://www.youtube.com/@Imphenzia) — Low poly speed modelling and game art

### Character Design
- [Nadiaxel](https://www.youtube.com/@nadiaxel) — Character concept and design fundamentals
- [Marc Brunet](https://www.youtube.com/@YourArtMentor) — Digital art and character design theory
- [Proko](https://www.youtube.com/@ProkoTV) — Figure drawing and anatomy (essential for character work)

### Game Mechanics & Design
- [Game Maker's Toolkit](https://www.youtube.com/@GMTK) — Deep dives into how game mechanics work
- [Design Doc](https://www.youtube.com/@DesignDoc) — Game design breakdowns and theory
- [Jonas Tyroller](https://www.youtube.com/@JonasTyroller) — Indie game dev and design thinking

### VR & AR Development
- [Valem Tutorials](https://www.youtube.com/@ValemTutorials) — Unity VR development from scratch
- [Dilmer Valecillos](https://www.youtube.com/@dilmerv) — AR and mixed reality with Unity
- [Justin P Barnett](https://www.youtube.com/@JustinPBarnett) — VR game development tutorials

### Game Engines (Godot & Unity)
- [GDQuest](https://www.youtube.com/@Gdquest) — Best Godot tutorials on YouTube
- [Brackeys](https://www.youtube.com/@Brackeys) — Unity tutorials (beginner to advanced)
- [KidsCanCode](https://www.youtube.com/@KidsCanCode) — Godot for beginners

